727139f-b.text:
Justice Ave., south side, between 90th street (left) and 55th Road (right), showing the boerum house, R.A. Boerum was the owner from 1873-1891.  Abraham G. Rapelye was the owner in 1820. Arthur White a photographer states this is the Vallance Boerum house, Erected by William Vallance about 1665. This is a set of four views; Nos. 3 and 4 being his work while Nos. 1 and 2 are by E.L. Armbruster.

May 1923
View 2: May 1929
Views 3 & 4: About 1927

Arthur White
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

725470f.text:
Fifty-sixth Ave. (formerly Court Street, also Justice Street), north side, east of 90th Street (about 160 feet), showing the J.S. Suydam house of 1860. Mrs. Taylor was the owner in 1873. Another occupant was Col. Bloom. This house was still standing in November
1923.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

725471f-a.text:
Fifty-sixth Ave., north side, east of 90th Street (Chicago Ave.), showing the J.5. Suydam House. See other views for more information.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

725472f-a.text:
56th Ave., north side, east of 90th Street (left, not seen). This
house is about 300 feet from the corner.
March 1923.
Eugene JL. Armbruster Collection.
